'''''Rayaru Bandaru Mavana Manege''''' is a 1993 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] romantic drama - action film directed by [[Dwarakish]] and produced by P. Balaram. The film stars [[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]]<ref>[http://www.vishnuvardhan.com/home.htm Vishnuvardhan film list]</ref> along with [[Farheen|Bindiya]] and [[Dolly Minhas]] in the prominent roles.<ref>[http://entertainment.oneindia.in/kannada/movies/rayaru-bandaru-maavana-manege/cast-crew.html Cast & crew]</ref> The music for the film was scored by [[Raj-Koti]] and the audio was bought by [[Lahari Music]].

The film is a remake of director [[Priyadarshan]]'s [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]] film ''[[Chithram]]'' (1988) starring [[Mohanlal]] and [[Ranjini (actress)|Ranjini]].<ref>[[Chithram|Chithram Wiki]]</ref>

==Cast==
* [[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]] (Vishnu) as a photographer 
* [[Farheen|Bindiya]] (Shivaranjini) as a photographers wife (moogi)
* [[Dolly Minhas|Dolly]] (Suma) as a rich women
* [[Dwarakish]] (Shyam) as a lawyer
* [[C. R. Simha]] (Ramachandra Rayaru) as rich women father
* [[Vajramuni]] as police officer
* [[Sihi Kahi Chandru]] as relative of rich women
* Shivakumar
* Vasanth Kunigal

==Soundtrack==
The music of the film was composed by [[Raj-Koti]]. The soundtrack consisted one [[Thyagaraja]] kriti "Nagumomu" performed by [[K. J. Yesudas]]<ref>[http://kannadasongs.allindiansite.com/rayaru_bandaru_mavana_manege.html Songs]</ref>

